CMA CGM Group, founded by Jacques R. Saadé, is a leading worldwide shipping & logistics group.

Now headed by Rodolphe Saadé, CMA CGM reinvents transport and logistics in order to offer an integrated maritime, port and land service that exceeds its customers' expectations.

Present in over 160 countries through 755 offices, 750 warehouses, equipped with a young and diverse fleet of 511 vessels, CMA CGM serves 420 of the world's 521 commercial ports and operates on more then 200 shipping lines. The group currently employs 110,000 people worldwide, including nearly 2,400 in Marseille, in its headquarters in Marseilles.

MISSION :
Provide support to the sales team to sell intermodal products and services;
Develop the transport of goods by road (to Cabinda, to Brazzaville, to Kinshasa);
Coordinate the development and monitoring of Bill of Lading Direct (BLD) traffic.
RESPONSABILITIES :
Development :
Identify any new business opportunities for the development of intermodal services;
Provide the sales team with tools to facilitate the sale of intermodal products/services: creation of advertising support, promotional material (product catalogues);
Welcoming and informing the customer about the products and services sold;
Manage road service providers : plan and distribute deliveries between BLD service providers: delivery of containers to CABINDA / DRC via BRAZZAVILLE / BRAZZAVILLE and major cities CONGO;
Elaborate sales statistics of BLD products; and report to the dedicated department of the Head Office.
BLD follow-up :
Identify all BLD by ship via LARA & GAIA applications;
Exploit the documentation received from POL, make sure it is complete;
Issue Transport Orders (TO) via LARA;
Follow up on the correct execution of deliveries;
Organize the delivery of containers to Cabinda/Kinshasa via Brazzaville;
To ensure the follow-up of the returns of empty containers in relation to Logistics;
Ensure the follow-up of BLD tracking updates;
Verify the dates of exit and departure of BLD containers from the port for the final destinations;
Provide the operation with a summary table of all BLD operations.
PROFILE :
According to the provisions of Article L122-1 of the National Service Code, only applicants aged between 18 and 28 years and European nationals will be eligible for this proposed mission in the form of a VIE.

You have 5 years of post-secondary education, you are specialized in commerce and/or maritime transport, and you have a perfect command of English.

Your thoroughness, excellent interpersonal skills and good ability to adapt to your environment are essential skills for this mission and will enable you to succeed fully in what is a springboard for a career within our Group.

Come along on CMA CGM’s adventure !

